This highlights that on average, women are paid 15.6% less than their male colleagues.  The 11.3% median 
average  indicates  the  mean  difference  is  reasonably  consistent  throughout  the  workforce  but  recognises 
that there are larger differences at the higher and lower end of earnings. 
 
 

 

 
 

